<id>http://forum.neoloader.com/viewtopic.php?t=3295&amp;p=16411#p16411</id>
<link href="http://forum.neoloader.com/viewtopic.php?t=3295&amp;p=16411#p16411"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Multihoster Support]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forum.neoloader.com/viewtopic.php?t=3295&amp;p=16411#p16411"><![CDATA[
Make it happen David. We know you're the king of features <img class="smilies" src="http://forum.neoloader.com/images/smilies/biggrin.png" alt=":D" title=":D" /> (your Neomule mods are awesome!).<br />Besides, I'm sure most people would choose a multihoster (if they know about it) instead of several single hosters.<br /><br />To start, integrate Zevera (download the API from the link above), test the plugin, make the UI newbie friendly, let Zevera know and they will give you the rewards <strong>&lt;&lt; Worth around 200-300GBP</strong>.<br /><br /><br />Request API from another multihosters (especially the one that support torrents ex. Real-Debrid, Alldebrid, Putdrive) and everybody benefit.<br />Pros: <br />1. For Multihosters: Obviously get more customers. And possibly save some bandwidth during peak hours.<br />2. For Torrents: Faster completed seeds, so it's easier for people to keep their ratio (on private tracker). And user most likely will keep the file shared; especially if they know it's on an anonymous network.<br />3. For ed2k: More completed chunks (lower ed2k queue <em>for other requested file</em> faster). And can help with current incomplete shares (if the hash matches).<br />4. For Neo: Jumpstarting the Neo Anon Network &lt;&lt; Very important. <br />5. For users: Faster download from multiple sources. Save resources, instead of opening several programs at once.<br />6. More popularity for your software and <em>attract more devs</em>, to help with bugs, features, etc.<br /><br />.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forum.neoloader.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3508">vezzie</a> — Tue Jul 09, 2013 6:29 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
