<content type="html" xml:base="http://forum.neoloader.com/viewtopic.php?t=3295&amp;p=16407#p16407"><![CDATA[
<blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />With a premium Multihoster account you can download from the supported hosters list, with all the advantages of the traditional premium account. The biggest benefit being that you only need to pay once instead of paying every single supported host.<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br /><strong>Apps that can successfully connect to multihosters:</strong><br />1. jDownloader : <a href="http://board.jdownloader.org/showthread.php?t=42131" class="postlink">Multihoster FAQ - JD Community</a> (Very good, lots of devs)<br />2. MiPony : <a href="http://www.mipony.net/en/features.php" class="postlink">Mipony - Features and advantages</a> (Very good, less RAM req)<br />3. Vity's FRD : <a href="http://wordrider.net/freerapid/plugins.html" class="postlink">FreeRapid Downloader :: FreeRapid Downloader - Plugins</a> (lots of plugins, very active devs)<br />4. JetDownloader (ok)<br /><br />From some of the programs above; you can look at the plugin source code if you need help connecting to the multihosters.<br />And some multihosters actually <em>rewards</em> you, if your software can connect to their service &gt;&gt; <a href="http://zevera.com/Downloader_Developers.aspx" class="postlink">Zevera Downloader Developers Information</a><br /><br />.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forum.neoloader.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3508">vezzie</a> — Sat Jul 06, 2013 11:16 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
